<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-536-723  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 536 723.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The New York Times  Oct 26 1990 v140 pC2(N) pD2(L) 13 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>U.S. proposes easing computer export curbs.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Markoff, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Computer industry officials and US allies are disappointed at theextent to which the US proposes to ease export controls oncomputers.andP;  The US is expected to announce its new restrictions ata meeting of the Coordinating Committee for Multilateral ExportControls (Cocom) in Paris at the end of Oct 1990.andP;  The newproposal is expected to allow the export of microcomputers butwill severely limit the export of workstations and other powerfulsystems.andP;  The government is divided over how much to easerestrictions with the Commerce Department and State Departmentfavoring an easing of restrictions while the Pentagon and NationalSecurity Agency seeking to restrain trade.andP;  Cocom is a group of 17Western allies and is attempting to ease trade restrictions toEastern Europe and the Soviet Union.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Coordinating Committee for Multilateral Export ControlsComputer industryMicrocomputersPolitical IssuesInternational tradeTechnology transfer.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>